\f0\b\fs56 \cf0 Grilled Flank Steak with Three Bean Salad                                                  
\b0\fs40 Serves 6\cell \lastrow\row
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\b\fs44 \cf0 INGREDIENTS\
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs50 \cf0 1/3 cup olive oil \
1/3 cup red wine \
1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar \
1 tablespoon Worcestershire sauce \
1 tablespoon soy sauce \
One 2-pound flank steak \
For Bean Salad: \
1/2 pound thin green beans, trimmed \
1/2 cup well-drained canned chickpeas \
1/2 cup well-drained canned dark red kidney beans \
1/3 cup olive oil \
1/4 cup red wine vinegar \
1 teaspoon sugar \
1 garlic clove, peeled, crushed through press \
1 cup loosely packed Italian parsley \
1/3 cup diced red onion\

\fs34 \
\pard\pardeftab720\ql\qnatural

\b\fs44 \cf0 DIRECTIONS
\b0 \

\itap1\trowd \taflags0 \trgaph108\trleft-108 \trbrdrt\brdrnil \trbrdrl\brdrnil \trbrdrr\brdrnil 
\clvertalt \clshdrawnil \clwWidth15260\clftsWidth3 \clmart10 \clmarl10 \clmarb10 \clmarr10 \clbrdrt\brdrnil \clbrdrl\brdrnil \clbrdrb\brdrnil \clbrdrr\brdrnil \clpadt40 \clpadl40 \clpadb40 \clpadr40 \gaph\cellx8640
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720
\cf0 FOR STEAK: 
\fs48 In a shallow, nonreactive dish, stir together olive oil, wine, balsamic vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce. Add steak and turn to coat. Cover and marinate at room temperature, turning once or twice, for 2 hours.\cell \row

\itap1\trowd \taflags0 \trgaph108\trleft-108 \trbrdrl\brdrnil \trbrdrr\brdrnil 
\clvertalt \clshdrawnil \clwWidth15260\clftsWidth3 \clmart10 \clmarl10 \clmarb10 \clmarr10 \clbrdrt\brdrnil \clbrdrl\brdrnil \clbrdrb\brdrnil \clbrdrr\brdrnil \clpadt40 \clpadl40 \clpadb40 \clpadr40 \gaph\cellx8640
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720
\cf0 Light a charcoal fire and let it burn down to hot. Position rack about 6 inches above heat source. Lay steak on rack. Cover and cook, turning once and basting with marinade from dish, until steak is cooked through, about 8 minutes total for rare meat. Transfer to platter. The steak can be grilled up to 2 hours ahead. Cover tightly and hold at room temperature.
\fs44 \cell \row

\itap1\trowd \taflags0 \trgaph108\trleft-108 \trbrdrl\brdrnil \trbrdrr\brdrnil 
\clvertalt \clshdrawnil \clwWidth15260\clftsWidth3 \clmart10 \clmarl10 \clmarb10 \clmarr10 \clbrdrt\brdrnil \clbrdrl\brdrnil \clbrdrb\brdrnil \clbrdrr\brdrnil \clpadt40 \clpadl40 \clpadb40 \clpadr40 \gaph\cellx8640
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720
\cf0 FOR BEAN SALAD: Cook green beans in large pot of boiling salted water until just tender, about 4 minutes. Drain immediately, transfer to a bowl of iced water, and when cool, drain well and pat dry. Cut beans crosswise into 1/2-inch pieces. Set aside.\cell \row

\itap1\trowd \taflags0 \trgaph108\trleft-108 \trbrdrl\brdrnil \trbrdrr\brdrnil 
\clvertalt \clshdrawnil \clwWidth15260\clftsWidth3 \clmart10 \clmarl10 \clmarb10 \clmarr10 \clbrdrt\brdrnil \clbrdrl\brdrnil \clbrdrb\brdrnil \clbrdrr\brdrnil \clpadt40 \clpadl40 \clpadb40 \clpadr40 \gaph\cellx8640
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720
\cf0 Toss chickpeas, kidney beans, oil, vinegar, sugar, and garlic in medium bowl. Season to taste with salt and pepper. The marinated bean mixture can be prepared several hours in advance. When ready to serve,  add green beans and onions to marinated bean mixture. Season salad to taste with salt and pepper. Finely chop parsley and sprinkle over salad. Serve at room temperature.\cell \row

